tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control (diabetes). Cholesterol and triglycerides are also elevated, suggesting increased cardiovascular risk. Renal function, electrolytes, and urine microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend optimization of diabetes and lipid management; no current evidence of renal impairment.
